videos.description: Louisville's Quentin Snider sets up Deng Adel for a two-handed alley-oop dunk.
videos.headline: Deng Adel throws down alley-oop slam

videos.description: Wake Forest's John Collins gets a block on defense and then gets down the court to score on a two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Wake Forest's John Collins has a block on one end and a dunk at the other

videos.description: Wake Forest's Bryant Crawford forces a Louisville turnover and makes a layup to give Wake Forest a 47-45 lead.
videos.headline: Wake Forest takes its first lead of the game

videos.description: Wake Forest's Bryant Crawford knocks down a step-back 3-pointer to give Wake Forest a 58-47 lead.
videos.headline: Wake Forest takes double-digit lead over Louisville

videos.description: Louisville's Deng Adel gets a steal and finishes with a fast-break dunk.
videos.headline: Deng Adel closes the gap after forcing a turnover

videos.description: Wake Forest's Mitchell Wilbekin hits a deep 3-pointer to give Wake Forest an 81-72 lead over Louisville.
videos.headline: Wake Forest connects on a deep 3-pointer late against Louisville

videos.description: Wake Forest pulls off the 88-81 upset win over No. 8 Louisville.
videos.headline: Wake Forest fans storm the court after upset Louisville
